    <section class="section-card">
      <h2 class="section-title">Career Highlights</h2>
      <p>
        At age 12, Birdy won the UK talent competition <em>Open Mic UK</em>, making her one of the youngest winners.
        Her breakout came in 2011, when at 14 she released a cover of Skinny Love (originally by Bon Iver), which became a hit across Europe.
        Since then she has released several studio albums including
      </p>

      <ul class="albums-list">
        <li><em>Birdy</em> (2011) — debut album with covers and original songs.</li>
        <li><em>Fire Within</em> (2013) — her second album showing more original work.</li>
        <li><em>Beautiful Lies</em> (2016) — explores growth and change.</li>
        <li><em>Young Heart</em> (2021) — more mature songwriting.</li>
        <li><em>Portraits</em> (2023) — her latest studio album as of 2023.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Her music has featured in major film soundtracks, and she has become known for her emotive voice,
        piano-driven arrangements and thoughtful lyrics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section-card">
      <h2 class="section-title">Style &amp; Influences</h2>
      <p>
        Birdy's style blends indie-folk, pop and piano-led arrangements.
        Because of her musical upbringing and early classical influences,
        she often brings a lush, cinematic feel to her songs.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
